ews/2018/07/23/alt-right-philosophy-white-identity-civil-rights/800232002/ |accessdate=March 3, 2019 |work=USA TODAY |date=July 28, 2018 |language=en |quote=The alt-right is a collection of '''far-right''' groups and people dedicated to \"white ethnonationalism\" in Western civilization, or the preservation of a white populace in Western countries.}}\n</ref>\n<ref name=\"NewYorker\">{{cite news |last=Wallace-Wells |first=Benjamin |title=Is the Alt-Right for real? |url=http://www.newyorker.com/news/benjamin-wallace-wells/is-the-alt-right-for-real |work=The New Yorker |date=May 5, 2016}}</ref>\n\n<!--<ref name=\"shapiro\">{{cite news |url=http://www.nationalreview.com/article/434548/conservative-intellectuals-george-nash-traces-history |title=The Conservative Intellectual Movement in America: Then and Now |work=[[National Review]] |first=Ben |last=Shapiro}}</ref>-->\n<!--<ref name=\"weeklystandard2\">{{cite news |url=http://www.weeklystandard.com/an-open-letter-to-mitt-romney/article/2002732 |title=An Open Letter to Mitt Romney |work=The Weekly Standard}}</ref>-->\n<ref name=\"cjrCheckmate\">{{cite web |url=http://www.cjr.org/analysis/alt_right_media_clinton_trump.php |last=Gourarie |first=Chava |work=Columbia Journalism Review |title=How the 'alt-right' checkmated the media |date=August 30, 2016}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"bostonglobe\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/arts/2016/08/28/what-alt-about-alt-right/QcKZ1A1u7Rxk7MSd69wU4M/story.html |title=What's 'alt-' about the alt-right? |first=Michael |last=Brodeur |publisher=The Boston Globe}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"unz\">{{cite web |url=http://www.unz.com/article/the-decline-and-rise-of-the-alternative-right/ |title=The Decline and Rise of the Alternative Right |work=The Unz Review |date=January 22, 2016 |accessdate=February 5, 2016 |last=Gottfried |first=Paul}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"reuters\">{{cite news |url=https://www.yahoo.com/news/clinton-accuse-trump-embracing-nativist-political-movement-102052962.html |title=Clin